Hello friends! I've been wanting to make a video like this for a while, there's so many great resources out there which can be on the more technical side that a lot of newcomers to Unreal won't know how to apply it to their own scenes. In this video we go over how to apply the amazing triplanar material function made by Visual Tech Art (link below) in the Megascans Master Material. I also go over how to apply displacement map to the Master Material.

Visual Tech Art's video: https://youtu.be/Cq5H59G-DHI?si=gAL_AqImHVqwx8KS
